,Recommended,215530,7933490,"Posted: 5 December, 2013",all,Tyrantsbane,"The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing lives up to it's title. It is pretty incredible.The core system of the standard ARPG is there and is solid. The twists it adds (such as the combo) system are fluid and innovative. The three classes seem balanced and conform to specific role types. While the maps aren't randomized, mob placement generally is. Playing on Hard, the mob packs were huge and plentiful.The quest line and atmosphere is wonderful. Some of the character models, when viewed up close, are kinda ""meh"". This doesn't matter because the environment is BEAUTIFUL. A lot of work went into creating this world, and it shows. There aren't many music tracks (they are generally recycled through different areas) but they are good and help immerse you into the world. As far as length, it took me about 20 hours to clear the campaign on Hard mode.I won't deny, there are some bugs to be worked out (Neocore is working on a patch as of this review) but they are hardly game breaking. The fact that this game was created out of a small company is incredible. The dev team is active with the player base on their forums and you can tell they generally care.If you have an ARPG crave, or you are trying to forget about the last few ARPG disappointments, you HAVE to play this game."
