,Recommended,215530,5056610,"Posted: 20 July, 2013",all,[slckr]robilar5500,"This game is incredibly fun. I'd say the closest game style wise and visually to compare it with would be Torchlight. However, Van Helsing has far more options in battle, and a bit of a deeper inventory system as well. The lootfest is definitely present, and the action is pretty much non-stop. The story is pretty well developed even though, as is often the case, it is sparse when compared to the outstanding gameplay. The levelling system is well balanced and requires a bit of thought.Graphically, I find this game to be a nice blend of the lush TL style with some better defined avatars. There are also nods to many movies in the game, most notably the Holy Grail and LOTR. You will find some Easter eggs along the way, which add a little levity to the game. Although the character interactions tend to be on the fun, sarcastic side, the story itself is somewhat dark, making it a nice blend of intensity and humor.For me, this game really hit the spot. An ARPG that really gets it right. If you are a fan of the game genre, this is a must play. Even if you arent, you should give it a shot. It's really that much fun!"
