,Not Recommended,215530,10328968,"Posted: 2 June, 2014",all,Mr. Yetti,"I really wanted to like this game, I really did.Positive:-Small development team, who made a playable (not really enjoyable) game. It's always nice to see little dev teams making games.-The starting price of $15 doesn't leave a bad taste in your mouth.-Clever take on Van Helsing, with some cool concepts.-I was expecting a pure text based game, with no voicework, yet I found the voicework to be better than some AAA games being released these days.-It's short and doesn't overstay it's welcome.-Decent replayabilityNegative:-The loading times are awful, they might be the worst loading times I've ever experienced in a game. There's also no loading indicator until 10 seconds prior to the next area loads up. So you're stuck looking at a boring map for 1-2 minutes, wondering if the game crashed.-This games default settings are ridiculous and slow down the game (newsflash the majority of PC gamers don't have crossfire video cards).-I found a few work arounds to speed up the load times to about 35-45 seconds but even then this game felt poorly optimized.-I have a pretty decent rig that can still play Far Cry 3, Skyrim, and Deus EX on high, with my frame rate rarely dropping below 35-45 fps. So why the hell can this game barely stutter by at 5 fps?? I haven't seen a game stutter and drop the framerate this much since my '07 gateway when I played WoW.-Oddly enough, I did find the frame rate to improve if I turned certain specs up not down (seriously).-The enviroments are generic, the same old muddy sewers/forest/foggy forest/cave, you've seen a million times in generic RPGs.-This game takes little to no strategy, I rarely died. When I did die, it was usually do to the screen stuttering and having my character jump across  the scene do to lag or a screen freeze.-The character models are pretty dull, you fight the same spiders/rats/zombies from every RPG. Although they do have some cool looking revolutionary robot soldiers and Van Helsing himself looks alright, even if he is a walking cliché.-Also for some reason the audio cuts in and out.-Gameplay is weird, they try to be so different from Diablo/Torchlight, that they remap certain keys and get rid of others altogether. All I wanted was another hack'n'slash diabloesque RPG, yet this game tries to reinvent the wheel and ends up making a square tire.Bottomline: This game is only worth picking up if it's part of some Humble Bundle or under $2. The forgettable story, boring graphics, frame rate issues, and loading screens will have you uninstalling this monster in less time then it takes to watch a trailer for that lame Van Helsing movie starring Wolverine.1/5"
