,Recommended,215530,7813065,"Posted: 28 November, 2013",all,pot roast,"I got this game for myself and a friend while it was on sale, and we've gotten some fun times out of it. My expectations were pretty low going in; I didn't really think that this game would be as much fun as it is. The writing and voice acting is pretty good, and I love the banter between your ghostly compainion, Lady Katarina, and Van Helsing.From a gameplay perspective, everything seems to be well thought out and well balanced, but there are certain aspects (like the combo system) that I didn't really understand for a while (probably because I disabled the tutorial). One of my favorite things about the game is just how hard it can be sometimes. There are certain enemies that can kill you in just a few hits, so it becomes really important to use potions all the time (but don't worry... they drop off of anything and everything so you will have trouble running out).One of the side-quests (to kill the hunter-machines) seems to be bugged for me, and I am not sure if all my skills are working the way they should (the upgrade to one of the skills should heal me each hit, but I can't really tell if it is working), but overall I love this game and think it's absolutely fantastic. The metascore clocks in at 72/100, which seems about right from a critical perspective, but the question I always ask myself is: Do I have fun playing this game, and how much fun am I having? The answer for The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing: Yes, this game is a blast and I am choosing to play it over the other games in my 181-game library on a nightly basis. Higly recommended for playing with friends (I haven't played solo)."
