76561198010700648,Not Recommended,215530,28899106,Posted: 1 January,all,Cerdwin,"I really wanted to like this game. I reallyreally enjoy RPG's of this type, so I thought this would be a good fit for me.The music is decent and the voice acting is straight on for the most part. I found a lot of cliched voicing, though, IE Count Vlados. However, the Romany girlthat you have to get flowers forsure doesn't sound like the other people in her camp.I found myself more than once cursing at the camera angles and apparently, fighting off screen is actually a thing if you're using a ranged character. And speaking of, I tried to melee my character. I really did. I usually play a tank type so it's not like I'm unfamiliar with it . . and. . . I ended up with a gun wielding character because that was the only thing I could find that would actually do damage and take down enemies without Van Helsing continually dying all the time. But because of this, omg, the sheer amount of kiting was amazing. I've never kited so much in a game as I did in this.Overall, the storyline was cliched as well. Mad Scientist, blah blah, Secret Lair (that's apparently not so secret) blah blah. And Easter eggs? Nah, they're fecking everywhere to the point that you actually get ""graded"" at the end of each chapter for how many you found. However, there's a lot of fun ""other game/movie/book"" references that make at least that portion a fun little romp.All in all, I'm giving this a 5/10 due to the negative points above. I suppose it'd be worth playing if you like the Van Helsing games. At the end of the day, though, if you're looking to purchase this one, DON'T. Go get the Final Cut version because this game is included as the first part of it. I bought this game and a friend of mine has Final Cut in their library so I was going to play that next. . . . and ended up playing the same game 2x in a row."
76561197995436761,Recommended,215530,8369156,"Posted: 28 December, 2013",all,jcaracc2003,"This is a very fun ARPG. The play mechanics are excellent, the maps are huge, the quests are fun, and, for a lower budget game, the voice acting is quite nice. There are two DLCs thus far and for those who have the game, the dev has offered a unique item and an aura as a thank you.Diablo, Torchlight, Grim Dawn, and other ARPG players will feel right at home with this game. There is a LOT of loot, a nice skill tree for your main character plus your ghost companion - she is a blast BTW with her snide and condescending remarks to Van Helsing. But, unlike the annoying companion in Legend: Hand of God, THIS companion is also a potentially gruesome, merciless killing machine. The DLC offers more replayability, but, even without it, you can play through the game again and specialize in different kinds of attacks - the same goes for your companion.This game LOVES to swarm you and enemies will attack in all directions - it's absolutely glorious and at times, loot drops can be almost as crazy as Torchlight II.I hope that Neocore will consider making a sequel. The game would easily compete with the best triple A ARPGs out there. A random map function would really round the game out.Props to the devs who have been VERY responsive and have kept this jewel up to date. I am an ARPG fanatic and The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing is one of the most fun I am still playing."
