76561197972507226,Recommended,215530,587931,"Posted: 2 June, 2013",all,-Ghost-,"A surprisingly solid action RPG. It reminds me a lot of Path of Exile or Titan Quest, along with the original Diablo 2. The skill trees have a moderate amount of depth, along with a torchlight style companion and reputation system that allows you to select special perks to benefit your character.. Skill trees are basically split into your standard magic, ranged and melee skills, plus 2 active ""trick"" abilities and 2 passive ""tricks"". My only gripe about the skill system is that you only really get to use 4 abilities at once (thought you can swap them out on the fly), so that may be dissapointing to those who like long  action bars of skills. The loot variety is fairly good, though you'll be sticking with greatswords, dual swords, pistols and long-barreled guns. Armor/weapon appearences also change as you get different gear, which is always nice. At the moment it sounds like the developers are going to be adding a lot of new content, with a new level 30+ scenario mode added for players who hit the level cap of 30, along with coop (already in) and future content planned such as a New Game +. Overall I was pleasantly surprised with this game, I haven't finished it yet at this time, but I've so far enjoyed the hours I've put into it, both with a ranged character and a a melee build."
