,Not Recommended,215530,30694477,Posted: 23 March,all,Felix,"The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing is a mildly fun medieval style RPG that doesn't take itself too seriously.  Call me a ""filthy casual"" if you will, but that sort of bugs me because it takes me out of the game a little bit. For example, the town portal system is called a ""wishing well"" a.l.a. Harry Potter with their magical fireplaces. So they make a joke about it saying that it is a fake & they should just call it a teleporter. I'm trying to get really into my medieval fantasy world here, guys! Why would you crack these little inside jokes like that. I get sort of a campy ""Monty Python comedy sketch show"" vibe from it. That is not a bad thing but it's just a different mentality I suppose. There is a character who you interact with who has a ""never lose"" mentality in this game. I get that it's a campy, sort of kooky kind of game that is just having fun with it. I just think of Van Helsing as a title that is for kids or perhaps young teens, as it is not serious enough. Like the Animorphs book series by K.A. Applegate, it is ""kid stuff.""A positive aspect of the game is that it is sort of along the lines of Diablo II or Diablo 3 but is set in 1700's Transylvania, instead. That is well & good but for a guy who has a couple hundred hours into D2 & a hundred or two into D3, that doesn't cut anything & doesn't seem impressive or convincing in the least. Basically this game is a disappointment if you are looking for some sort of alternative to the Diablo franchise of RPG games from the company Blizzard, Inc, but better. I suppose it is ok for what it is. Not a popular game. I play a swashbuckling gothic pirate type of person who swoops through the scene every month or so & kills all the rats & evil spiders & such.Final conclusion can be summed up thusly: ""Meh, it's OK."" Not really a showstopper or barnburner or ""game that changed the WORLD forever"" or anything like that. The graphics are a bit old. I haven't played a whole lot of the game. 6/10 would buy but only if it were HEAVILY discounted & there was nothing going on on a Saturday afternoon or Friday evening after working the ol' day job. It does go good with a Starbucks Latte, so that's something I guess. Visiting ASU there in AZ at the moment. On second thought, now that I think about it, save your money. DON'T buy Van Helsing!"
