,Recommended,215530,7357727,"Posted: 10 October, 2013",all,Dr. Strange,"Top down action games are not usually something I choose.  However, every time I saw this game, it seemed intriguing to me and I must admit that I really like the cover art. (Not a reason to buy a game, I know) When I read some reviews to try and find out what it was like, it seemed that everyone was disatisfied with it.  However, when I finally got it and started to play, I find that I really like it a lot.  Plus, no suprise, but everything that those reviewers didn't like, I like.  They complained about the leveling system, how convoluted it was and that most of the skills were meaningless.  Well, anyone who has played the later FF games will feel right at home here. All of the skills and perks are interesting and well balanced so that you really have to think about what you want to choose or level up.  The game did seem really hard at first.  But, once I learned to play it properly (meaning to use all the tools I am given) then it became much more engrossing and fun.  Another reviewer complaint was the humor in the game.  There is a lot of really dry, tongue in cheek banter between Van Helsing and his ghostly companion.  I really like it and it never reaches annoying levels.Finally, there is a lot of detail in the game and you can zoom in far enough to actually be able to appreciate it.  Visually, all of the locations are exceptionaly well created.  The level designs are also well laid out with huge amounts of detail.  There are a mondo amount of items that can be used, exchanged, modified, crafted and so on.  So, as you can tell, I really like it a lot.I have not really found an engrossing story yet, but I feel I still have a lot to play.  Also, sometimes, the other voice actors can be pretty extreme.  But those two things are really minor as far as I am concerned.So, you might pick it up when you are in the mood for that kind of game."
