76561198035386144,Recommended,215530,9347719,"Posted: 4 March, 2014",all,thorvaaldr,"For my ARPG playing friends, one of Steam's Midweek Madness items is Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing, a steampunk Diablo clone set (very loosely) in the world of the over-the-top 2004 Stephen Sommers movie.Is it perfect? Of course not. But it is one of my favorites of the current generation of Diablo clones. Almost as much wander-fight-loot-level-up fun as Torchlight II, with a much more focused plot and storyline, and a setting that is NOT one more dragons, castles, elves and such Standard Western Fantasy World (tm).AND, it has a downloadable demo, so you don't have to take my word for it - try it, and see if YOU like it.If anyone is wondering - if you do pull the trigger, YES, spend the extra $1.70 (or how over many groats or whatever it is overseas) for the Complete Pack with the DLCs. Yes, they are, basically, making you pay money to get access to ALL the ""character classes"". Think of it like Diablo II's LoD expansion - maybe it SHOULD have been in there to start, but it wasn't, and it DOES make the game much more interesting."
