76561198055762608,Recommended,215530,16408940,"Posted: 14 June, 2015",all,Ortzz,"This game is janky, but a good kind of janky. It is a little bit broken, not super creative, very campy, but a whole lot of fun.I would say though that the best thing about the game is that it is self aware and knows that it wants to be a game where you use Van Helsing to slay thousands of monsters. This game lacks creative risks that would make it groundbreaking, but it instead focuses on making you feel like a badass monster slayer by using tried and true action rpg mechanics. This is elivated by the world of Van Helsing, which is filled with mechanical werewolfs, broken zepplins, revolutionary vampires, and of course your creepy russian ghost sidekick. Environments were not always super varied, but they were often well crafted and worth exploring, filled with loot and strange minions. It also helps that every part of almost every map is just filled to the brim with monsters, meaning you pretty much always had something to do. Sure, a game with a lot of combat is not super creative, but enimies were just different enough that I would need to use different strategies to kill them and the thrill of watching a bunch of loot explode out of them was just inspiering enough to make it all seem worthwhile.One thing worth mentioning is how much game this offers. I played through the game exactly once and that is where I plan to stop, but there is a new game plus mode and an endless mode of some sort. I'm not sure what they are, but the amount of content you get for the price is pretty good (maybe not rpg standards, it's not 80 hours afterall), so I certainly would pick it up during a sale if you just want an action game that will take your time.It is one of those rare games that gets better as you play it, the combat really opens up when you have a bunch of moves and the banter between Van Helsing and his ghost partner actually becomes pretty funny from time to time. I left the game glad I had spent the time I did with it, and looking forward to playing the other ones in the franchise. If you want a campy yet solid ARPG, get this."
