,Recommended,215530,12367458,"Posted: 4 October, 2014",all,Faris,"Without a doubt, my favorite dungeon crawling game. Everything is done right. It has a linear story with slight control over a few things for the immersion factor. The UI is highly functional and easy to understand. The skill trees have no pitfalls and let you build the player as they want, yet it won't give you everything. On normal mode, it's a perfect balance between easy and hard, always providing a challenge. The characters are charming and offer a lot of humor. It has some easter eggs referencing Lord of the Rings and Monty Python, but does it in a way that won't make you shake your head in disappointment, like some other action RPGs.... *cough* BL2 *cough*. Even the achievements gave off of the right kind of vibe to where you feel actually accomplished by getting one, and have the motivation to get others. The art direction is fantastic, and the graphics look beautiful. Though, it's endorsed by NVIDIA, so it may not run as smoothly using AMD parts due to some sneaky hardware lock-outs. I'd recommend this game to anyone who loves Diablo or Victorian/Gothic fiction.You even get a spunky ghost sidekick"
