,Recommended,215530,9156434,"Posted: 17 February, 2014",all,The Owl,"The Future Generations of what we used to know as kids- Diablo Game.In this great graphics game, you will never feel bored or that alone playing it as this is mainly a single payer game.What makes it this way is all thanks to the character development of the katarina 'ghost' who follows you around and assist you in battles. She was designed to be a humorous and engaging companion throughout this game. The voice accent and story is quite well planned out. Its her interaction with you that makes the game a whole new level unlike in diablo where you wander around in the woods with yourself and your erm, mud monsters who doesn't talk.I started with the complete pack demo kit on 'normal' mode'. Which was great since the monster aren't too overpowering that might make you give up playing the game. Afterall, you wanna just enjoy playing & finish the game story not engraging yourself trying so hard to kill the monsters. Or actually, them killing you. Another great thing is that you can respawn on the same spot you died by paying 'coins'. Gone are the days where dying means restarting the whole mission and having to walk all the way back for the same battle. In saying this , note that you will be a invisible ghost for few seconds, allowing you to move around before respawning as a human and meanwhile still being chased by the monsters that once killed you before...Weapons & skills are fun & have a pretty acceptable range to choose from. The abilitys and skills are too not advanced nor complicated, to me as a 21 years old (Girl) gamer.  Another plus point.Recommended for people who don't want to go for the games that is too addictive such as team fortess which you can play hours after hours trying to kill people without any objective really. For somewho like me who have a full time job commitment but is a young adult that would like to enjoy a simple yet satisfing & engaging game, this is the one.P.S i searched so hard on steam & finally found it <3P.S [Part 2] I finished the game within two weeks. So i must say the story is kinda short. And there is not point purchasing those arcane classes stuff. Becos there isnt really a 'never ending story'. They said that becos in reality , it means restarting the game with different class but same map, monester & story. And God, that is boring as hell!!"
