,Recommended,215530,8310687,"Posted: 26 December, 2013",all,fiduke27,"Starts off decently. The way it pigeonholes you into choosing ways to play ensures lots of playthroughs to experiment with different playstyles. But, due to limited level advancement, you can never overpower the enemies you play against. In fact once you hit the cap, it becomes a strategy game more than an action game, due to the limited resources to distribute. Get it wrong and you'll just die a lot.This game has an excellent foundation, but totally whiffs on the foundation of the diablo genre. It's fun to become crazy awesome over time. If you make a game where I have limited resources and can never overpower the enemies, then it becomes a strategy game with diablo playstyle. And since it's basically a strategy game, you have to have creative enemies and encounters. It doesn't. It has repetitive waves of monsters that you fight through. So in that essence it's a bad strategy game.In short, you'll have a fun time starting out. As the game progresses though, it turns into a horrible strategy game. I give it 8/10 to start, and finishes around 4/10. I'll average that out for overall score.6/10"
