,Recommended,215530,8569422,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,fLx,"Brief review:The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing is a really solid action-RPG with the same level of polish and story as other post-Diablo 2 games in the genre such as Titan Quest and Path of Exile. Highlights for me were:* The power-up system that had you do a little more thinking about what buttons to press when;* Your companion, Lady Katarina, who not only offers more customisation options, but also provides grin-worthy banter with your protagonist; and* The various design decisions that lead to a much more streamlined ARPG experience, including being able to toggle monster respawn, sending Katarina back to town to sell weapons, the 'sell all' and 'organise' inventory buttons, and much more.Recommended for any fans of the Diablo series that were disappointed with D3 and are looking for a cheap, well-themed alternative (and don't want to be part of the hardc0re ARPG scene with Path of Exile).Podcast:To hear a podcast with extended impressions on this game, tune in to its episode onTim and Phill Talk About Games:http://www.timandphill.com/2013/12/24/taptag-006-bram-stokers-brains-edition/"
