,Recommended,215530,12379544,"Posted: 5 October, 2014",all,Seasoned Wanderer,"The Incredible Adventures Of Van Helsing is a great game. You, Abraham Van Helsing (Son of the great Van Helsing we know), is out doing his fathers work to continue the legacy on in this epic game. Fight across different landscapes such as dark caves filled with spiders, a town filled with twisted beasts and machinery, swamps with unknown creatures, and so much more. And if you thought you was doing all of that monster slaying on your own, you're not. With your compainion Lady Katarina. She may be a ghost but she sure packs a punch or three. She has three different forms Melee, Ranged, and Ghost. The first two are self explainitory but the last one is that she doesn't attack instead she gives you a 10% damage buff. There is also Skills for you and Katarina such as life steal, to paralyzing your foes, to blowing them up, and more. Also when you level up you can increase four different stats for the both of you Willpower, Dexterity, Body, and Luck. Also when you kill enough enemies you can choose a perk that will give you strong bonuses. There is also enchanments and essence you can put on your weapons and gear to make them more powerful. As well as two different fighting options for Van Helsing. Ranged which include Shotguns, Rifles, and Pistols. And Melee which is Swords. I would gladly give this game a 10/10. And the replay value is pretty high because after you beat the story you can redo it with the NeverEnding Story option for more and better enemies and loot."
