76561197972621243,Recommended,215530,8031775,"Posted: 13 December, 2013",all,ONION,"A nice looking ARPG with steampunk elements thrown in for flavour.You battle your way through hordes of monsters that all look good and all die in satifying ways. The maps are all created as opposed to randomly generated. This mankes for a good forst time experience - and a rather bland second playthrough - can't say if the third playthrough is even more boring, I don't think anybody ever got that far.In case you get lonely -you have your trusty sidekick with you - Katarina the ghost. I liked her, the comments from her are actually funny and you are never alone while killing monsters. She can fight for you, gather loot, buy potions etc. A really nice addition and she even comes with a full skilltree.There are lots and lots of loot and the whole-loot end of the game is quite allright.Aaaaand... Then theres all the annoying stuff like. Getting lost in the game and having to backtrack - I swear that some areas become unaccesable in the game so you can't go back there and finish a quest.The game itself - the monsterkilling is done with a maximum of 6 skills (unless you want to tab between skillsets - I don't think anybody does that. I ended up with two skills - a single target and a sweep - and that's it... hour after hour...The mobs themselves are pretty and fit the theme - but killing them gets kinda boring - especially when you end up with the ones slowing you. The only tactics that are in the game is positioning - and when a mob slows you (nothing you can do about it) positioning gets annoying.And then there are the bugs... In my first playthrough (and the game had been out forever at that time) I had to manually skip an endlevel encounter with a code to get on and then at one point I had to wait several days because U couldn't enter the next area - bad to asy the least - it's not an early acces game...Then there is the tower defense mode wich is horrible. Imagine a towerdefense where YOU are one of the little guys in the maze.. yop... You are running around in your maze defending. It's boring the defense quests are too long the only good thing is that after two encounters you are done. Two... why go through the whole business of making it and then only have 2 quests? Maybe because it's boring, but then remove it all together...Did I have fun for around 14 hours? Yes would I recommend it? Yes - but it's not the new Diablo I, II or III."
