76561197970582726,Recommended,215530,8046386,"Posted: 14 December, 2013",all,cazychel,"The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing (Nth Review)This game is better than Diablo 3. Okay, that was too easy...This game is better than Torchlight 2. There you go!And indeed I like it much better than TL2. The world of ""Helsing"" is a steampunk-ish one with a little bit of the old classic Diablo gothic horror atmosphere, combined with many throwbacks to horror classics in film and literature. The graphic style reflects that very well, being less cartoonish than D3 and TL2, while still being colorful enough to avoid monotony. The sound and voice acting are very good, just not outstanding.The story is nothing special, but avoids being too generic via its strong characters and some interesting side quests. Especially the humor of this game is brilliant with a lot of jokes within the world, as well as on ARPGs and games in general.In terms of gameplay this game delivers a big chunk of ARPG goodness with different playstyles, an interesting NPC partner (a ghost!) and lots of customisation for your gear and skills. The monsters require different tactics and the balance is very fair, but can be hard sometimes.Rating: Very recommendable!"
