76561198009257676,Recommended,215530,11311315,"Posted: 18 July, 2014",all,lancelot64,"!!!!!Posted without DLC!!!!!Extremely addicting Action RPG. You play as Abraham Van Hellsing, son of the famous Vampire Slayer. The non-DLC game is extremely interesting as you have 2 different sets of talent trees, that not only supply you with abilities that you can unleash upon the myriad different enemy types, you also have a set of auras that increase your combat capabilities, as well as tricks(spells) that have a variety of different effects.At it's core, this is a simple Action RPG, you kill monsters, you complete quests, and you get gold/gear so that you can ruin the day of the next monster that crosses your path. The overall atmosphere in the game is quite refreshing, Van Hellsing isn's some armored knight for justice, he's a monster hunter, pessimistic, sarcastic, and interesting to play.Your companion/pet in the game is a ghost called Lady Katerina, with her own unique talents/spell combinations, she is a very good compliment to VH's grounded sense of gun/swordplay.Reccomend this to any fan of Diablo or Torchlight, as they play almost exactly the same. The trees are more expansive then Diablo 3, at least imo, but  not quite the same llevel of customization as the trees in Torchlight.VERDICT: Good Game. I enjoy it tremendously."
,Recommended,215530,2083145,"Posted: 23 July, 2013",all,Tiwill,"Pros:If you were a fan of Diablo 2, but were disappointed by Diablo 3 because of its lack of stat distribution, its straightforward skill system and its auction house, and were a bit put off by the cartoony art style of Torchlight (it doesn't really fit this genre in my opinion), then you will enjoy Van Helsing, because the mechanics are pretty close to Diablo 2.Cons:Once you complete the game, you realize there is no variety in it, and no replay value. There are only 2 types of melee weapons and 2 types of ranged weapons (fast & slow), and the skills are pretty boring and not really apparent, you basically use mana and rage to make your attacks more powerful, and that's about it. At the beginning of the game, it looks like there are many skills to choose from, but then you realize there are only 4 legit builds: tank melee, spellcaster melee, DPS ranged and spellcaster ranged.So... it's still a great game if you like action RPGs, but don't expect anything near Diablo 2 or you might be disappointed. I'd give it an 8/10."
