,Recommended,215530,7627500,"Posted: 10 November, 2013",all,MrAptronym,"A surprisingly good ARPG, with high production value for an indie. The writing is sometimes funny and quirky, but too often falls into tired tropes and old memes. The game looks great, with solid sound design backing it up. The powers are varied enough to try a multitude of builds, and cheap respecs and ample equipment encourage trying a few out. Most of the powers feel great too, lightning bolts have a thunderous retort, and sword slashes feel quick and deadly.Sadly only the basic (But highly adaptable) hunter class is included, the other two classes are DLC. They have fewer skills but are more focused on particular play styles. If you decide to play the game, I strongly suggest you play on the hardest, 'heroic', difficulty; the game isn't very difficult and you will get much better loot."
