,Recommended,215530,26425538,"Posted: 4 November, 2016",all,Zozzero,"Played 12hrs in local single:People! Don't miss this! Have you ever wanted to get humor at every corner while you play in a standard ARPG structure? This is it! Good graphics, very good music, out of the box dialogues. No, you will not face groundbraking (Reminding you, this game was released in 2013) features, no toplist demanding content....in the regular way. BUT! This game was made out of FUN, and that comes through! If you want to get entertained, this game is for you.I have played full Diablo series, Immortal Throne, Neverwinter, MMOs(, Magicka - who played it, will get it)... this game picks up the succesful features from all of them, put in one place, twist a bit, and spice it up. On first sight I underestimated it, but have no fear, it will deliver suprises, monster slaying and Fun!Just a few feature, that felt very good:- You can set your companion (ghost) to collect items, drink poiton (and what rate), how to deal with the enemies, and needs skill point distribution.- You can spend your level-up points or redistribute it while you have the window open. If you still want to reconsider, you can redistribute in town at NPC.- There are each different aspect features of skills also, available for skill points.- You can choose fame perks, which will also affect your skill outputs.- Items have ""rune"" capacity (it is even further expandable), so you can load them up as you wish.- some puzzles, conundrums, and TD also indluded.For those, who are familiar with movies and gaming, liked Sherlock Holmes (2009, 2011) musics, likes sitcom in RPG, and want to slay monsters in a world with mindblower monsters, this is a musthave! Currently 15 EUR, and for that price, you shouldn't miss it."
