76561198045282909,Recommended,215530,26411712,"Posted: 4 November, 2016",all,Mr. Rogers,"Here's a short run down of first impressions of the time i've played it.Pros:-Gritty 1800's European fantasy-Witty banter/conversations between characters-Decent voice acting-Decent, well shaded graphics-Deep, in-depth ability and class trees-Top notch leveling system (with leveled enemies)-Easy to learn, easy to play-Fitting music-Side quests that don't make you feel like you're doing a choreCons:-Lack of variety for playable classes-Because of previous con, lack of variety in weapons-Little to no costume/character customization-I'm biased because I like character customization in my gamesI got it for $5.00 on sale and I would say it was definitely worth it, but I wouldn't go so far as to say it's worth more than that. Definitely a good game for anyone who loves the ARPG genre, though."
