76561198007846731,Recommended,215530,28814945,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,GrimmReaper,"If you like ARPG's then you should give this a go. It has all the hallmarks of the classic games within this genre:* Puzzles to find and solve by exploring and taking not of the environment* Riddles to answer* Random sidequest you are throw into due to events that happenned* Booby-trapped chest which sees you fighting for you live with no where to run* Listening to npc chatter can lead you on a quest for treasure* Quests have multiple outcomes depending on the choice you make* The banter and chit chat between the protaganist and Katrina is entertainingInitially the combat seems ovewhelming and you spend most of the time running around avoid trying to die, however once you grasp how the mechanics, skills, attributes, perks etc all fit together it becomes a different game and you happily waltz into hoardes of monsters and annilihate them all. Do a bit or research to understand the game and you will be good to go and start your monster hunting career."
