,Recommended,215530,34691613,Posted: 2 September,all,YoynK,"Give this game a shot if you are into advanced hack and slash: I really enjoy this game. It has an immersive atmosphere, color, sound and voice acting. I particularly enjoy the dynamic between Helsing and his companionion Katarina.There is great variation in mobs to fight in this hack and slash, prospective projection rpg. The number of unique item drops is a handful to sort through, almost infinite variation (if this sort of thing appeals to the player).The system requirements are a bit steep and the game is poorly optimized. However, If one has a gtx 760 or better they should be able to enjoy the game at 30 fps or above on highest graphic settings. The controls can get a bit messy or maybe overwhelming for new players.I look forward to playing through this game again on a different skill tree as well as in sequal games in the ""Final Cut"" of Van Helsing."
